                    "body": "Assigned to Bill",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-15T13:44:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-15T13:44:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25831",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue steems from a badly engineered switching between ZEND and GNU Modes.\n\nZend_Console_GetOpt works with two modes on options MODE_ZEND and MODE_GNU. What happens in the above example is the following:\n\nIn the constructor arguments are created in MODE_GNU. Console_GetOpt recognizes that and reverts its setting from MODE_ZEND (default) to MODE_GNU. Now when the addRules() is called with v|verbose Console_GetOpt is still in MODE_GNU and tries to add the array accordingly which fails.\n\nThe fix for this issue is very simple and just consists of not switching to MODE GNU when first adding a string then an array.\n\nI suggest a refactoring to strategy pattern to fix the strange switch statement. I will add an issue for this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-07T06:01:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-07T06:01:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
